# UI and Styling

- Use Uniwind (Tailwind CSS for React Native) via `className` prop — never inline `style` for colors, spacing, or layout
- Theme is driven by `@layer theme` with `@variant light` / `@variant dark` in `src/global.css`. Colors switch automatically; **do not** use `dark:` variants for theme tokens
- Use design tokens from `global.css`: `text-content-primary`, `text-content-secondary`, `text-content-tertiary`, `bg-fill-primary`, `bg-fill-secondary`, `bg-fill-tertiary`, `border-border-tertiary`, `text-brand-primary`, `text-critical-primary`, and semantic aliases `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-primary`
- For dynamic style values (e.g. `placeholderTextColor`), use `useCSSVariable('--color-*')` from `uniwind` or `useAppTheme()` from `@/components/app-theme`
- Reusable UI components live in `src/components/ui/` (Button, Card, Container, Badge)
- Wallet-specific components live in `src/components/wallet/`
- Screen containers use `<Container safe>` for SafeAreaView + themed background
- Spacing: Tailwind scale (`p-4`, `mb-6`, `gap-4`, etc.)
- Border radius: `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `rounded-full` (tokens in `global.css`)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — design tokens, no dark: prefix (theme switches via Uniwind)
<View className="bg-fill-secondary p-4 rounded-lg">
  <Text className="text-content-primary text-base">Hello</Text>
  <Text className="text-content-tertiary text-sm">Subtitle</Text>
</View>

// ❌ BAD
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#f8fafc', padding: 16, borderRadius: 12 }}>
  <Text style={{ color: '#0f172a', fontSize: 16 }}>Hello</Text>
</View>
```
